    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presented in Carbon Black Metallic, this 2002 BMW M3 (E46) is a museum-grade example of the marque's engineering pinnacle. Power is derived from the S54 3.2L inline-six engine, featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure VANOS variable valve timing system that pulls cleanly to an 8,000 RPM redline. This chassis has undergone proactive subframe reinforcement and a rod bearing service to ensure structural and internal longevity. The powertrain is mated to a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-spec M-variable differential lock for optimal torque distribution. Riding on staggered 19-inch Style 67 forged wheels with fresh Michelin Pilot Sport 4S rubber, the suspension geometry remains tight with no bushing deflection. This is a turn-key, collector-quality specimen with a documented service history and zero deferred maintenance.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
